          "title": "Coins missing from wallet and blockchain",
          "body": "After mining ~67 clear coins on the z9 network, and receiving 2 coins from a member on the Slack channel, my coins have gone missing!\n\nIt isn't apparent yet whether this is due to some fault of my own, or if there is a bug in the software somewhere. Still trying to track down the source of the issue. \n\nLocal wallets in zcashd and the public block explorer report zero balances for both accounts, and show no previous transactions. It's as if the accounts never existed, or were never used.\n\nI was able to salvage a small amount of ZEC in some encrypted notes, and will try to perform JoinSplits with those to test their existence on the blockchain.\n\nThe public addresses in question are:\nmiJz3Yz4Jqm1YMoKiUy77pjqL56WBQd18C\nmogaz8qa4sBKWCyHvUJNDQgwXw1izMbGw2\n",
